WEBVTT

1
00:00:02.135 --> 00:00:06.664
<i>Carroll was convicted in 2004 for
the murders of 14 young women.</i>

2
00:00:06.874 --> 00:00:09.810
<i>We need you in Virginia.</i>
RYAN: I'm not an agent anymore.

3
00:00:09.977 --> 00:00:12.617
<i>You caught Carroll. No
one knows him like you do.</i>

4
00:00:12.679 --> 00:00:15.879
- So what's my sequel about. Joe? CARROLL:
<i>We're gonna write this together. Ryan.</i>

5
00:00:17.851 --> 00:00:19.786
Even though you
slept with my wife.

6
00:00:19.987 --> 00:00:23.424
I have so many
surprises waiting for you.

7
00:00:23.657 --> 00:00:26.320
Olivia. I require legal counsel.

8
00:00:26.527 --> 00:00:29.895
- Do not bring me into this any further.
- We're just getting started.

9
00:00:32.032 --> 00:00:33.591
You wanna see Joey. get in now.

10
00:00:33.834 --> 00:00:35.496
I was told I'd see
my son. Where is he?

11
00:00:35.702 --> 00:00:38.399
You don't have to be afraid
of me. Claire. Trust me.

12
00:00:38.605 --> 00:00:39.903
Hey. Joey. Remember me.

13
00:00:41.642 --> 00:00:43.372
Do not move.

14
00:00:45.379 --> 00:00:46.574
Be right back.

15
00:00:47.948 --> 00:00:50.110
The place is surrounded
by cops. No way out.

16
00:00:50.350 --> 00:00:52.376
Come on. We gotta go.

17
00:00:52.586 --> 00:00:54.054
What's taking them so long?

18
00:00:54.254 --> 00:00:56.655
I looked all over the place.
She and Joey are both gone.

19
00:00:58.058 --> 00:01:00.186
- Don't move.
- Joey. we're here to help you.

20
00:01:01.695 --> 00:01:03.755
- Ah.
- I'm with Roderick. Let's go.

21
00:01:04.031 --> 00:01:05.624
Stop right there. No.

22
00:01:05.866 --> 00:01:07.892
Joey. no. Wait.

23
00:01:29.222 --> 00:01:30.246
Where are we?

24
00:01:32.960 --> 00:01:34.986
I thought we were
going to see my mom.

25
00:01:35.228 --> 00:01:38.289
We are. But I need
to meet a friend first.

26
00:01:38.498 --> 00:01:40.126
We have to meet
your friend here?

27
00:01:40.400 --> 00:01:43.996
Yes. He's going to help
us. okay? I won't be long.

28
00:01:44.237 --> 00:01:46.934
What about Jacob and
Paul? Aren't they coming too?

29
00:01:49.276 --> 00:01:50.505
I don't know.

30
00:01:51.745 --> 00:01:54.271
What about the bad guys?
Aren't they looking for us?

31
00:01:54.481 --> 00:01:55.972
- No.
- How do you know?

32
00:01:56.450 --> 00:01:57.474
Joey please. stop.

33
00:02:01.655 --> 00:02:05.649
Everything's going
to be okay. Promise.

34
00:02:16.003 --> 00:02:17.266
Hello.

35
00:02:18.605 --> 00:02:20.096
I've been waiting for you.

36
00:02:24.811 --> 00:02:26.336
I was told to come here.

37
00:02:26.546 --> 00:02:30.278
I know. It's about
time you showed up.

38
00:02:32.552 --> 00:02:33.986
My name is Bo.

39
00:02:35.055 --> 00:02:36.648
Go pull your truck in there.

40
00:02:37.024 --> 00:02:38.822
I have to go use the bathroom.

41
00:02:39.459 --> 00:02:43.521
We've been driving all night.
You got a little boy's room?

42
00:02:44.931 --> 00:02:45.955
Through the office.

43
00:02:49.202 --> 00:02:50.465
Go ahead. Joey.

44
00:03:19.332 --> 00:03:20.391
Hello?

45
00:03:48.228 --> 00:03:52.893
Please. Please. Help me.
Please. Don't leave me here.

46
00:03:53.100 --> 00:03:58.403
Don't leave me. Please. Come
back. Come back. Come back.

47
00:04:11.651 --> 00:04:14.553
<i>Hey. Come on. come on.</i>

48
00:04:14.755 --> 00:04:18.283
Ryan Hardy's assault
resulted in three broken fingers.

49
00:04:18.525 --> 00:04:22.758
As I'm sure you're aware. warden. it's a clear
violation of his Eighth Amendment rights.

50
00:04:22.963 --> 00:04:24.261
I'm aware.

51
00:04:24.464 --> 00:04:25.955
FBI's behavior was unwarranted.

52
00:04:26.166 --> 00:04:29.762
We have case law precedents.
federal tort and civil liberties claims...

53
00:04:29.970 --> 00:04:33.031
Just exactly what do
you want. Miss Warren?

54
00:04:33.240 --> 00:04:35.232
I'll let my client
tell you himself.

55
00:04:36.042 --> 00:04:37.135
Mr. Carroll?

56
00:04:38.478 --> 00:04:45.043
First. um. Warden Montero
and other important people...

57
00:04:45.252 --> 00:04:51.624
thank you. thank you for allowing me
the opportunity to share the injustices...

58
00:04:51.825 --> 00:04:56.160
that have been
inflicted upon me.

59
00:04:59.699 --> 00:05:04.137
He said his name was Charlie
and that he was hired to follow me...

60
00:05:04.337 --> 00:05:05.771
and to report back to Joe.

61
00:05:05.972 --> 00:05:10.307
He had photos and video and he
said he was going to take me to Joey.

62
00:05:10.510 --> 00:05:11.637
And you believed him.

63
00:05:11.845 --> 00:05:13.211
Yes. I did.

64
00:05:14.181 --> 00:05:15.513
He had this honor about him.

65
00:05:15.715 --> 00:05:19.413
Like he was living up to some
code of conduct. Definitely military.

66
00:05:22.556 --> 00:05:24.684
Um. Marines or
Army or something.

67
00:05:24.891 --> 00:05:28.453
He said he was waiting to hear from
someone named Roderick for orders.

68
00:05:28.662 --> 00:05:30.392
Tea?

69
00:05:32.833 --> 00:05:33.994
Thank you.

70
00:05:34.668 --> 00:05:35.692
Roderick?

71
00:05:35.902 --> 00:05:37.598
Um. yeah. I'm
sure it's an alias.

72
00:05:37.804 --> 00:05:40.831
Roderick Usher is from Poe's
<i>Fall of the House of Usher.</i>

73
00:05:41.041 --> 00:05:44.239
We were at the farmhouse.
Emma got a call from this Roderick.

74
00:05:44.477 --> 00:05:46.639
Cult leaders often have
a second in command.

75
00:05:46.980 --> 00:05:49.211
Someone to oversee
who manages the cult.

76
00:05:49.416 --> 00:05:52.011
Do you even know how many
people are involved in this?

77
00:05:52.485 --> 00:05:55.045
Are we talking fans
or prison groupies?

78
00:05:55.255 --> 00:05:59.317
Or people with serious mental disorders?
Do we know how many of them have killed?

79
00:05:59.526 --> 00:06:02.860
We don't know. It's a lot bigger
than we thought. More pervasive.

80
00:06:03.063 --> 00:06:06.625
Ms. Matthews? Can I count on you
not to engage with Joe's followers?

81
00:06:06.833 --> 00:06:09.997
No. you can't. No more than I
can count on you to find my son.

82
00:06:10.203 --> 00:06:11.728
Claire...

83
00:06:12.839 --> 00:06:15.138
I don't know what I
would do in your situation.

84
00:06:15.575 --> 00:06:19.910
So I would just ask you to inform us if
anyone makes contact with you again.

85
00:06:28.688 --> 00:06:30.418
You have to find
this guy. Charlie.

86
00:06:30.657 --> 00:06:32.649
- I'm sorry...
- Don't. Just find him.

87
00:06:33.526 --> 00:06:34.960
He knows where they took Joey.

88
00:06:50.243 --> 00:06:51.370
When is Charlie coming?

89
00:07:05.892 --> 00:07:07.087
There you are.

90
00:07:09.062 --> 00:07:10.223
You okay?

91
00:07:13.099 --> 00:07:14.123
Hey.

92
00:07:14.734 --> 00:07:16.202
Everything okay. honey?

93
00:07:16.403 --> 00:07:18.599
There was a girl locked
in a cage back there.

94
00:07:18.805 --> 00:07:21.400
- She's scared. We have to help her.
- There's a what?

95
00:07:21.608 --> 00:07:25.340
- We have to help her.
- You're not supposed to go back there.

96
00:07:27.080 --> 00:07:28.571
She's none of your business.

97
00:07:33.320 --> 00:07:34.652
You don't go back there.

98
00:07:36.022 --> 00:07:37.081
Okay?

99
00:07:38.525 --> 00:07:39.618
You understand?

100
00:07:47.534 --> 00:07:48.763
Stay right here.

101
00:07:50.537 --> 00:07:52.233
Why do you have
the girl in a cage?

102
00:07:53.540 --> 00:07:57.272
- Is there something I should know about?
- It's none of your business neither.

103
00:07:59.612 --> 00:08:01.171
Why don't we just wait?

104
00:08:02.482 --> 00:08:03.780
Less talking.

105
00:08:05.318 --> 00:08:07.184
Just wait.

106
00:08:10.123 --> 00:08:11.363
You can't do this. Gene.

107
00:08:11.524 --> 00:08:13.823
I've already discussed
it with Director Franklin.

108
00:08:14.461 --> 00:08:18.762
I understand some lines may have been
crossed. but this doesn't make any sense.

109
00:08:18.965 --> 00:08:20.490
He's a convicted serial killer.

110
00:08:20.700 --> 00:08:25.400
Carroll makes a convincing case for prison
abuse. I don't need that kind of liability.

111
00:08:25.638 --> 00:08:26.662
What's going on here?

112
00:08:26.873 --> 00:08:30.139
Look. just give me the time to
speak with the Justice Department.

113
00:08:30.343 --> 00:08:33.370
- Find a better alternative.
- It's too late for that. Excuse me.

114
00:08:33.580 --> 00:08:37.312
And I'd suggest you do something about
this man before he does more damage.

115
00:08:37.517 --> 00:08:39.884
This is on you. Mr. Hardy.

116
00:08:41.388 --> 00:08:43.380
What is he talking
about? What's going on?

117
00:08:43.590 --> 00:08:46.526
The warden just granted Joe
Carroll's request for a transfer.

118
00:08:46.726 --> 00:08:48.524
- He's leaving.
- What? When?

119
00:08:48.728 --> 00:08:52.096
Immediately. They're
preparing to move him now.

120
00:09:04.444 --> 00:09:07.437
Joe Carroll. You have been
remanded into the custody of the...

121
00:09:07.647 --> 00:09:11.049
Jesup County Federal Correctional
Facility in the state of Georgia.

122
00:09:15.155 --> 00:09:16.214
Mind giving us a room.

123
00:09:17.424 --> 00:09:18.448
He's all yours.

124
00:09:23.263 --> 00:09:25.494
I don't believe we've
had the pleasure.

125
00:09:27.000 --> 00:09:29.367
Ah. Ryan. Come
for your farewell visit.

126
00:09:30.370 --> 00:09:31.394
Thanks.

127
00:09:35.742 --> 00:09:38.769
Well. I couldn't let you leave
without saying a proper goodbye.

128
00:09:38.978 --> 00:09:44.781
So why the transfer. Joe? What's in
Georgia. huh? You have friends there?

129
00:09:46.186 --> 00:09:49.623
Is that where the cult is?
Your good buddy. Roderick?

130
00:09:50.123 --> 00:09:53.651
Roderick? Roderick. No. Sorry.

131
00:09:54.394 --> 00:09:57.091
Name doesn't ring a
bell. Tell me about Claire.

132
00:09:57.964 --> 00:10:02.993
How did she react when you failed
to rescue our son? Was she upset?

133
00:10:03.436 --> 00:10:05.098
Has she rejected you yet?

134
00:10:06.539 --> 00:10:11.034
It's okay. Ryan. Every great
love must be tested. after all.

135
00:10:11.277 --> 00:10:12.472
You know. that's strange.

136
00:10:14.147 --> 00:10:17.777
I say the name Roderick. and
you immediately change the subject.

137
00:10:18.952 --> 00:10:21.649
I'm so gonna miss
these little chats.

138
00:10:24.991 --> 00:10:26.857
We need to take him
down for processing.

139
00:10:39.873 --> 00:10:41.307
Goodbye. Ryan.

140
00:10:42.809 --> 00:10:45.870
I want to go. I think that I
should be supervising the transfer.

141
00:10:46.079 --> 00:10:49.982
U.S. Marshals are supervising the transfer.
They agreed to let me accompany them.

142
00:10:50.150 --> 00:10:52.176
- No. Listen. I gotta be there...
- You can't.

143
00:10:52.852 --> 00:10:53.876
Look.

144
00:10:54.487 --> 00:10:58.219
I know we're all upset and disappointed
about what happened at the farmhouse.

145
00:10:59.893 --> 00:11:01.259
But we got this.

146
00:11:02.462 --> 00:11:04.192
I will make sure
nothing goes wrong.

147
00:11:14.874 --> 00:11:15.898
Mike.

148
00:11:17.710 --> 00:11:19.076
What's up?

149
00:11:20.079 --> 00:11:22.207
I need you to look
into Warden Montero.

150
00:11:22.615 --> 00:11:24.481
The warden's been compromised?

151
00:11:24.684 --> 00:11:26.949
I don't know what to
think. Something's not right.

152
00:11:27.120 --> 00:11:28.850
Mm.

153
00:11:38.198 --> 00:11:39.598
So how do you know Roderick?

154
00:11:42.502 --> 00:11:45.028
I do things for him
from time to time.

155
00:11:45.638 --> 00:11:46.936
What kind of things?

156
00:11:57.917 --> 00:11:59.146
Are you still in there?

157
00:12:00.220 --> 00:12:02.917
I'm Joey. I got the
keys. Let me get you out.

158
00:12:03.256 --> 00:12:06.420
- Joey. I'm Dana.
- Nice to meet you.

159
00:12:08.127 --> 00:12:09.652
I knew you'd come back.

160
00:12:15.235 --> 00:12:18.637
- Do you know Joe Carroll?
- I know who he is.

161
00:12:19.339 --> 00:12:21.171
But I'm not a part
of his little club.

162
00:12:26.579 --> 00:12:29.276
- Where's the kid?
- Joey?

163
00:12:30.650 --> 00:12:32.141
Joey?

164
00:12:35.488 --> 00:12:36.979
- Please hurry.
- I am.

165
00:12:37.290 --> 00:12:38.588
You can do it.

166
00:12:42.595 --> 00:12:43.995
Got it.

167
00:12:48.268 --> 00:12:49.292
Come on.

168
00:12:54.574 --> 00:12:57.066
What are you
waiting for? Let's go.

169
00:13:08.855 --> 00:13:09.879
What did you just do?

170
00:13:10.790 --> 00:13:11.951
Why did you do that?

171
00:13:13.660 --> 00:13:15.629
Why did you do that?

172
00:13:17.497 --> 00:13:18.863
You come back here.

173
00:13:24.871 --> 00:13:26.362
Come here.

174
00:13:26.606 --> 00:13:28.165
Get back here.

175
00:13:33.646 --> 00:13:35.478
Where are you?

176
00:13:45.858 --> 00:13:46.917
Joey.

177
00:13:53.833 --> 00:13:56.029
Hey. Joey. I'm
not gonna hurt you.

178
00:13:59.939 --> 00:14:01.737
I'm not gonna hurt you.

179
00:14:05.545 --> 00:14:07.013
Come here.

180
00:14:07.680 --> 00:14:09.410
I told you not to go back there.

181
00:14:09.649 --> 00:14:11.948
Why did you do that?
Why did you do that?

182
00:14:12.185 --> 00:14:13.710
Touch him again and you're dead.

183
00:14:18.091 --> 00:14:19.457
Joey. come here.

184
00:14:22.895 --> 00:14:24.227
Denise.

185
00:14:25.298 --> 00:14:26.732
Unh. Joey. run.

186
00:14:35.375 --> 00:14:36.735
What the hell is going on?

187
00:15:16.616 --> 00:15:17.845
Everything okay out there?

188
00:15:18.084 --> 00:15:20.815
All set. Chopper's inbound now.

189
00:15:23.222 --> 00:15:25.657
Okay. They're locking
him in the transport vehicle.

190
00:15:30.129 --> 00:15:32.792
Prisoner is in the transport.
Securing all doors now.

191
00:16:02.762 --> 00:16:04.628
Hey. What did you find out?

192
00:16:04.831 --> 00:16:09.428
He looks clean. No known associations
with anybody that's visited Joe Carroll.

193
00:16:09.635 --> 00:16:13.629
But I did find one thing. The warden's
got a teenage daughter enrolled in college.

194
00:16:16.008 --> 00:16:19.035
- You thinking what I'm thinking?
- Yeah.

195
00:16:19.645 --> 00:16:20.874
Warden Montero?

196
00:16:21.113 --> 00:16:24.515
- I don't have time. Hardy.
- A question about Joe Carroll's transfer...

197
00:16:24.750 --> 00:16:26.742
- We've already been through this.
- Humor us.

198
00:16:26.953 --> 00:16:28.979
You're the reason that
man got transferred. Not me.

199
00:16:29.188 --> 00:16:32.488
Okay. So this has nothing to
do with your daughter. Dana?

200
00:16:32.692 --> 00:16:35.127
- Where is she. warden?
- She's in school.

201
00:16:35.761 --> 00:16:36.785
Hoberman College.

202
00:16:37.063 --> 00:16:39.862
- That's right. WESTON: She
hasn't been to class in two days.

203
00:16:40.066 --> 00:16:43.264
Her boyfriend filed a missing
persons report with campus security.

204
00:16:43.469 --> 00:16:45.199
I wasn't aware.
I'll look into it.

205
00:16:45.404 --> 00:16:47.305
Joe Carroll's people
threatened you.

206
00:16:47.740 --> 00:16:49.580
They forced you to
authorize his transfer. huh?

207
00:16:49.609 --> 00:16:50.702
Mr. Hardy...

208
00:16:51.177 --> 00:16:54.170
I understand you're here
at the behest of the FBI...

209
00:16:54.680 --> 00:16:58.139
but you're skating on very
thin ice. Do not push me.

210
00:17:06.025 --> 00:17:07.823
- You buying it?
- Not for a second.

211
00:17:08.027 --> 00:17:11.862
I want to know everything about him.
Where he goes. Who he talks to. Everything.

212
00:17:19.071 --> 00:17:20.437
What's taking so long?

213
00:17:21.541 --> 00:17:23.806
We're waiting for word
that it's safe to move.

214
00:17:24.010 --> 00:17:25.535
But why do we have to wait here?

215
00:17:26.178 --> 00:17:27.942
What about that guy. Bo?

216
00:17:28.681 --> 00:17:30.013
Is he part of this?

217
00:17:31.050 --> 00:17:34.043
When we set up the website.
we found a lot of people like Bo.

218
00:17:34.453 --> 00:17:36.422
Useful. but in a limited way.

219
00:17:36.822 --> 00:17:40.850
He's not a part of everything.
And he won't be coming with us.

220
00:17:41.060 --> 00:17:42.460
He's got that girl in a cage.

221
00:17:42.695 --> 00:17:44.561
The girl is very important.

222
00:17:45.765 --> 00:17:47.859
Her name is Dana.
She's our leverage.

223
00:17:48.067 --> 00:17:50.536
She's going to ensure we
make it home safe tonight.

224
00:17:52.872 --> 00:17:54.101
You know the people there?

225
00:17:54.340 --> 00:17:55.535
A few.

226
00:17:56.142 --> 00:18:00.705
Some of my buddies that I signed
up with. Friends of Roderick's.

227
00:18:00.947 --> 00:18:03.576
What about your friends?

228
00:18:04.450 --> 00:18:07.716
Uh. Paul and Jacob.
What happened to them?

229
00:18:14.493 --> 00:18:18.760
I'm sorry. I didn't mean to...

230
00:18:24.403 --> 00:18:26.304
We do what we have to do.

231
00:18:37.249 --> 00:18:38.512
Run it again.

232
00:18:42.021 --> 00:18:43.080
What's up?

233
00:18:43.289 --> 00:18:46.316
Going through the stuff we
confiscated from Charlie's warehouse.

234
00:18:46.525 --> 00:18:49.518
I found surveillance footage.
One was marked Detention Center.

235
00:18:49.762 --> 00:18:51.253
- It's from here?
- Mm-hm.

236
00:18:52.431 --> 00:18:55.765
Well. it's the prison's exit. Why
would Charlie have video of that?

237
00:18:57.837 --> 00:18:59.931
You have access to
surveillance footage...

238
00:19:00.139 --> 00:19:02.335
of Joe Carroll's transfer
vehicle as he left?

239
00:19:02.541 --> 00:19:06.308
- Ah. yes. I think I do.
- Pull it up. Same point. Exiting Sally port.

240
00:19:09.482 --> 00:19:12.111
There. Look at
that. Run that back.

241
00:19:12.852 --> 00:19:14.013
Enhance that.

242
00:19:14.453 --> 00:19:17.321
There. That's an edit.

243
00:19:21.961 --> 00:19:24.487
The warden hijacked
the surveillance footage.

244
00:19:24.697 --> 00:19:27.531
The warden just left the
building. He's taking the day off.

245
00:19:27.733 --> 00:19:29.429
Get Parker on the phone now.

246
00:19:38.978 --> 00:19:40.002
Agent Parker.

247
00:19:40.179 --> 00:19:41.490
<i>Joe's not in the
transport vehicle.</i>

248
00:19:41.514 --> 00:19:44.348
- What are you talking about?
- Stop transfer. Check the truck.

249
00:19:44.550 --> 00:19:46.678
<i>- He's not in there.</i>
- That's impossible.

250
00:19:46.886 --> 00:19:50.152
The warden and his men
have been compromised. Do it.

251
00:19:51.257 --> 00:19:53.954
- We need to stop. Check on the prisoner.
- Why?

252
00:19:54.193 --> 00:19:55.593
Stop. Now.

253
00:20:12.278 --> 00:20:13.337
Open up.

254
00:20:18.017 --> 00:20:20.111
- What's going on?
- Open the vehicle.

255
00:20:20.352 --> 00:20:23.186
- I'm not authorized to do that.
- I'm authorizing you.

256
00:20:23.355 --> 00:20:24.914
Heh. that's not how it works.

257
00:20:25.124 --> 00:20:27.719
It's not a request.

258
00:20:40.372 --> 00:20:42.102
What the hell is your problem?

259
00:20:44.543 --> 00:20:45.704
What did you do?

260
00:20:45.911 --> 00:20:48.244
I don't know what
you're talking about.

261
00:20:55.020 --> 00:20:56.215
Open the trunk.

262
00:20:58.958 --> 00:21:01.894
- You're gonna get my daughter killed.
- Open the trunk.

263
00:21:33.025 --> 00:21:35.051
Where is he?
Where the hell is he?

264
00:22:01.387 --> 00:22:03.447
Thank you. Olivia.

265
00:22:11.130 --> 00:22:13.964
She's my daughter.
They're gonna kill her.

266
00:22:14.333 --> 00:22:15.392
They won't.

267
00:22:15.634 --> 00:22:18.160
They need her alive to
guarantee Joe's safety.

268
00:22:18.337 --> 00:22:19.896
So just tell us what you did.

269
00:22:20.139 --> 00:22:23.371
And we can save your
daughter and stop Joe.

270
00:22:31.817 --> 00:22:36.517
His lawyer. Olivia Warren. They
told me to hand Joe off to her.

271
00:22:42.428 --> 00:22:43.487
Cuff him.

272
00:22:49.401 --> 00:22:52.132
We need a location for Olivia
Warren. Joe Carroll's lawyer.

273
00:22:52.338 --> 00:22:54.773
Tell Mitchell to ping Warren's
cell. It's our best chance.

274
00:22:55.007 --> 00:22:57.033
Tell Boy Wonder
thanks. I'm already on it.

275
00:22:57.243 --> 00:22:59.508
- She's already...
- Yes. no. I heard.

276
00:23:00.512 --> 00:23:03.676
Found it. She's in Richmond.
Driving. Headed southeast...

277
00:23:03.883 --> 00:23:06.352
- on 12th Street toward Carey Ave.
- Great.

278
00:23:06.552 --> 00:23:07.576
I'll call for back-up.

279
00:23:07.786 --> 00:23:09.846
- Southeast.
- Yeah. I heard that too.

280
00:23:17.463 --> 00:23:19.398
You seem a bit nervous. Olivia.

281
00:23:20.666 --> 00:23:27.402
That's because I'm presently committing
at least seven felonies. How much further?

282
00:23:27.973 --> 00:23:29.703
Just a few more minutes.

283
00:23:40.319 --> 00:23:41.378
Hey.

284
00:23:42.721 --> 00:23:44.451
You're not supposed
to be out here.

285
00:23:46.091 --> 00:23:50.324
- Denise thinks I'm reading my book.
- Hmm.

286
00:23:50.496 --> 00:23:53.330
She said you're gonna
take me to see my mom.

287
00:23:53.565 --> 00:23:55.261
Doesn't sound
like you believe her.

288
00:23:57.469 --> 00:24:00.598
She's telling you the truth. I
was just with your mom. you know.

289
00:24:00.806 --> 00:24:03.469
- You were?
- Yup. She wouldn't stop talking about you.

290
00:24:03.709 --> 00:24:06.269
I was supposed to bring
her here so you could see her.

291
00:24:06.478 --> 00:24:07.707
What happened?

292
00:24:09.782 --> 00:24:10.806
I screwed up.

293
00:24:11.850 --> 00:24:15.480
And. uh. let the bad
guys get in the way.

294
00:24:17.656 --> 00:24:18.851
Is she okay?

295
00:24:19.758 --> 00:24:23.661
Oh. yeah. Yeah.
Yeah. She's fine.

296
00:24:24.797 --> 00:24:30.498
It's just gonna take a little bit
longer before you can see her.

297
00:24:31.003 --> 00:24:33.268
Okay. I'm sorry about that.

298
00:24:34.473 --> 00:24:35.771
Okay.

299
00:24:36.742 --> 00:24:40.440
Will you tell me the truth?
What's really going on?

300
00:24:43.382 --> 00:24:44.873
What do you want to know?

301
00:24:45.284 --> 00:24:47.879
That girl. Will she be okay?

302
00:24:51.991 --> 00:24:55.359
Will it make you feel better if
I promise you she'll be okay?

303
00:24:57.129 --> 00:24:59.291
Yeah? Okay.

304
00:24:59.498 --> 00:25:02.832
I give you my word. All right?

305
00:25:10.376 --> 00:25:11.810
Is this where you need to be?

306
00:25:12.277 --> 00:25:13.677
Yes.

307
00:25:14.413 --> 00:25:19.283
- I don't think anyone followed us.
- Ah. I admire your positive attitude. Olivia...

308
00:25:19.485 --> 00:25:22.011
but I don't share your optimism.

309
00:25:22.388 --> 00:25:26.849
There is. uh. one more
thing I need you to do for me.

310
00:25:27.059 --> 00:25:28.220
What is it?

311
00:25:29.661 --> 00:25:31.357
Call Ryan Hardy.

312
00:25:31.563 --> 00:25:35.295
- What? Why would I?
- Do it.

313
00:25:47.746 --> 00:25:49.305
<i>FBI dispatch.</i>

314
00:25:49.515 --> 00:25:53.919
Hello. This is Olivia Warren. I need to
speak to Ryan Hardy. It's an emergency.

315
00:25:54.219 --> 00:25:56.211
<i>I'll connect you now.</i>

316
00:26:00.692 --> 00:26:02.627
- Hello?
- Mr. Hardy?

317
00:26:02.861 --> 00:26:05.092
Olivia. Where are you?
Is Joe Carroll with you?

318
00:26:05.330 --> 00:26:08.459
Say these exact words to him.

319
00:26:08.834 --> 00:26:12.896
Joe Carroll is killing me
and it's because of you. Ryan.

320
00:26:13.105 --> 00:26:15.734
- What?
- Tell him that I am killing you...

321
00:26:15.941 --> 00:26:18.342
<i>- and it's because of him.</i>
- Don't do it. Joe.

322
00:26:18.544 --> 00:26:20.069
- Wait. Olivia.
- Please. No...

323
00:26:20.279 --> 00:26:22.111
Put Joe on the phone with me.

324
00:26:22.347 --> 00:26:26.409
- Tell him. Olivia. Tell him it's all his fault.
- I won't!

325
00:26:26.618 --> 00:26:29.349
- What's going on?
- Tell him he can kill me.

326
00:26:30.889 --> 00:26:33.586
Olivia? Olivia? OLIVIA: <i>No.</i>

327
00:26:35.794 --> 00:26:40.425
<i>No. Wait. Wait. I'm gonna
be there soon. He can kill me.</i>

328
00:26:42.000 --> 00:26:45.732
<i>Olivia. Olivia.</i>

329
00:26:46.271 --> 00:26:48.900
Hello? Hello?

330
00:26:49.108 --> 00:26:51.668
<i>No. no. no.</i>

331
00:26:53.011 --> 00:26:56.641
- No.
- Hardy. Hardy.

332
00:27:51.136 --> 00:27:52.502
FBI!

333
00:27:56.141 --> 00:27:57.404
Anybody see anything?

334
00:27:57.576 --> 00:27:59.477
Guy got out of the
car and ran in there.

335
00:28:00.479 --> 00:28:01.947
Right. call 911.

336
00:28:07.352 --> 00:28:08.581
Do you see him?

337
00:28:08.820 --> 00:28:10.152
Go that way.

338
00:28:28.840 --> 00:28:31.366
I'm David. It's a pleasure. sir.

339
00:28:33.412 --> 00:28:35.540
Weston. He's up there.

340
00:28:36.915 --> 00:28:40.579
Get out of the way. Come
on. FBI. Stay back. Stay back.

341
00:28:42.621 --> 00:28:45.284
This way. sir. This way.

342
00:28:51.863 --> 00:28:52.887
Take that side.

343
00:28:53.098 --> 00:28:54.122
All right. Move.

344
00:29:07.879 --> 00:29:11.008
- What are you...
- Excuse me.

345
00:29:30.535 --> 00:29:32.060
I'm Louise. sir.

346
00:29:35.641 --> 00:29:38.304
It's nice to meet you. Louise.

347
00:29:40.178 --> 00:29:42.977
<i>Douglas. are you in
the basement? Over.</i>

348
00:29:43.181 --> 00:29:46.618
<i>Douglas. Douglas. do you copy?</i>

349
00:30:34.633 --> 00:30:38.468
Oh. this is most baffling.

350
00:30:39.037 --> 00:30:42.906
You. me. us. Here
in this moment.

351
00:30:43.875 --> 00:30:49.007
What do I do? I kill
you? Huh? Now?

352
00:30:51.583 --> 00:30:53.381
Hmm?

353
00:30:53.552 --> 00:30:56.647
No. This is...
This is all wrong.

354
00:30:57.322 --> 00:31:00.656
No. You can't die in a parking
garage. That would be most uneventful.

355
00:31:00.859 --> 00:31:02.828
- Hardly dramatic at all. heh.
- Go ahead.

356
00:31:04.663 --> 00:31:06.154
Do it.

357
00:31:07.632 --> 00:31:10.397
You must admit. It's
a quandary. hmm?

358
00:31:10.902 --> 00:31:16.864
I so very much want
you to live and see...

359
00:31:17.409 --> 00:31:19.173
all that's about to happen.

360
00:31:20.879 --> 00:31:25.078
You see. as much as you've
encountered up until this moment. heh...

361
00:31:25.350 --> 00:31:29.720
Well. I don't know how to tell you
this. but we have only just concluded...

362
00:31:29.921 --> 00:31:34.552
the first part of our
novel. Yes. Ryan...

363
00:31:34.760 --> 00:31:39.562
for nine long years I
have sat in my prison cell...

364
00:31:39.765 --> 00:31:44.465
outlining this entire
story in my mind.

365
00:31:45.470 --> 00:31:50.408
I've meticulously planned all of it.
With a little help from my friends.

366
00:31:52.244 --> 00:31:54.770
That's a Beatles
reference by the way.

367
00:31:57.549 --> 00:32:02.487
And I must say. heh. it is very
much going according to plan.

368
00:32:06.458 --> 00:32:08.051
We should leave now. sir.

369
00:32:10.195 --> 00:32:13.688
There is so much
more to come. Ryan.

370
00:32:17.469 --> 00:32:18.698
I'll be in touch.

371
00:32:21.239 --> 00:32:24.300
Call me when you're
gone. And then I'll let him go.

372
00:32:30.315 --> 00:32:32.750
Don't even think about it.

373
00:32:37.289 --> 00:32:40.350
You can't kill me. Didn't
you hear what Joe just said?

374
00:32:41.760 --> 00:32:43.285
He wants me alive.

375
00:32:44.162 --> 00:32:46.154
Then I'll shoot you in the leg.

376
00:32:47.332 --> 00:32:48.356
Don't miss.

377
00:33:41.720 --> 00:33:44.815
Okay. Yeah. we'll be on
the road in a few minutes.

378
00:33:45.557 --> 00:33:48.584
We're clear to go. Ah. It's gonna
take us a few hours to get there.

379
00:33:49.728 --> 00:33:51.026
What about him?

380
00:33:53.431 --> 00:33:54.592
And the girl?

381
00:33:57.168 --> 00:33:59.296
Give me a few
minutes. I'll be right back.

382
00:34:06.945 --> 00:34:08.311
You need anything else?

383
00:34:09.047 --> 00:34:10.515
We need a word in private.

384
00:34:11.116 --> 00:34:12.175
Anything wrong?

385
00:34:12.384 --> 00:34:15.411
No. Just some
unfinished business.

386
00:34:29.868 --> 00:34:34.135
The helicopter wasn't registered.
Airport radar had them for a short time...

387
00:34:34.372 --> 00:34:35.704
but they lost them.

388
00:34:36.274 --> 00:34:38.436
Warden Montero
is in federal custody.

389
00:34:38.643 --> 00:34:40.578
- Anyone locate his daughter?
- Not yet.

390
00:34:40.779 --> 00:34:42.611
How do we find these people?

391
00:34:42.847 --> 00:34:46.443
- They're nameless. Faceless.
- We'll find them and break them.

392
00:34:50.488 --> 00:34:53.253
Let's start with
this guy. Right now.

393
00:34:53.458 --> 00:34:55.222
I can't let you hurt him. Ryan.

394
00:34:55.427 --> 00:34:59.159
If we're gonna end this. find
Joe. find his son. the rest of them...

395
00:34:59.397 --> 00:35:01.730
we gotta do things
a different way.

396
00:35:13.078 --> 00:35:14.410
I'll give you five minutes.

397
00:35:24.189 --> 00:35:26.317
Guys. Listen up.

398
00:35:28.293 --> 00:35:32.321
Fellas. I need to
speak with him.

399
00:35:42.273 --> 00:35:45.937
So. The boy.

400
00:35:46.277 --> 00:35:51.113
Joey Matthews. Where is he?

401
00:35:55.453 --> 00:35:57.945
I'm not going to
tell you anything.

402
00:36:01.793 --> 00:36:03.318
You look like you're in pain.

403
00:36:03.528 --> 00:36:04.962
I can handle it.

404
00:36:09.334 --> 00:36:10.700
That's good to know.

405
00:36:41.966 --> 00:36:44.834
- Use the bolt cutters. WESTON:
We found the warden's daughter. FBI.

406
00:36:45.036 --> 00:36:48.302
- I'm gonna get you out of there alive.
- Bring in the paramedics.

407
00:36:50.508 --> 00:36:55.742
Okay. Okay. We got you now. Okay
now. You're okay. We got you. We got you.

408
00:36:56.781 --> 00:37:00.479
Hey. Hey. Look at me.
There was a little boy...

409
00:37:01.219 --> 00:37:06.715
Joey. They. they took him. He
was... He was trying to help me.

410
00:37:09.027 --> 00:37:11.292
The place is clear.
She's the only one.

411
00:37:12.897 --> 00:37:16.527
It's okay now. Come on.
we'll get you out of here.

412
00:37:31.416 --> 00:37:34.318
Did they tell you where I'm
going? Because they won't tell me.

413
00:37:34.552 --> 00:37:37.112
Protective custody.
It's better if I don't know.

414
00:37:42.293 --> 00:37:43.955
- So Joe's free...
- Claire...

415
00:37:44.229 --> 00:37:45.629
And now I get locked up.

416
00:37:48.800 --> 00:37:50.029
It's for your own safety.

417
00:37:51.836 --> 00:37:53.236
And my son?

418
00:37:53.438 --> 00:37:54.667
I'm not giving up. Claire.

419
00:37:55.640 --> 00:37:57.074
That's what he wants.

420
00:37:57.776 --> 00:37:59.244
But he's not going to win.

421
00:38:01.279 --> 00:38:02.907
This isn't a game. Ryan.

422
00:38:03.114 --> 00:38:06.812
This is my life.
This is my son's life.

423
00:40:10.742 --> 00:40:11.766
Come on.

424
00:40:14.312 --> 00:40:15.371
It's okay.

425
00:40:48.513 --> 00:40:49.572
Hey. Joey.

426
00:40:52.150 --> 00:40:53.641
I know you.

427
00:40:55.353 --> 00:40:56.821
You're my Dad.

428
00:41:02.327 --> 00:41:03.590
Yeah.

429
00:41:04.128 --> 00:41:05.756
Yeah. I'm your dad.
